{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idb8fb1298-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s925B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"925B"},"text":"§ 925B.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Reporting of background check denials to State authorities","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb8fb1299-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s925B/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"In General","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"If the national instant criminal background check system established under section 103 of the Brady Handgun Violence Prevention Act (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t34/s40901"},"text":"34 U.S.C. 40901","children":[],"tail":") (referred to in this section as “NICS”) provides a notice pursuant to section 922(t) that the receipt of a firearm by a person would violate subsection (g) or (n) of section 922 or State, local, or Tribal law, the Attorney General shall, in accordance with subsection (b) of this section—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8fb129a-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s925B/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" report to the local law enforcement authority of the State or Tribe where the person sought to acquire the firearm and, if different, the local law enforcement authorities of the State or Tribe of residence of the person—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8fb129b-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s925B/a/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" that the notice was provided;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8fb129c-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s925B/a/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the Federal, State, local or Tribal prohibition;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8fb129d-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s925B/a/1/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the date and time the notice was provided;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8fb129e-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s925B/a/1/D"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"D"},"text":"(D)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the location of the licensee where the firearm was sought to be transferred; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8fb129f-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s925B/a/1/E"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"E"},"text":"(E)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the identity of the person; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8fb12a0-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s925B/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" where practicable, report the incident to State and local prosecutors or Tribal prosecutors in the jurisdiction where the firearm transfer was sought.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb8fb12a1-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s925B/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Requirements for Report","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"A report is made in accordance with this subsection if the report is made under subsection (a) within 24 hours after the NICS denies a firearm transfer in accordance with ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t18/s922/t"},"text":"section 922(t) of title 18","children":[],"tail":", United States Code, except that the making of the report may be delayed for so long as is necessary to avoid compromising an ongoing investigation."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb8fb12a2-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s925B/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment of Report","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"If a report is made in accordance with subsection (b) and, after such report is made, the Federal Bureau of Investigation determines that the receipt of a firearm by a person for whom the report was made would not violate subsection (g) or (n) of section 922 or State, local, or Tribal law, the Attorney General shall notify any law enforcement authority and any prosecutor to whom the report was made of that determination.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb8fb12a3-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s925B/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Rule of Construction","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"Nothing in subsection (a) shall be construed to require a report with respect to a person to be made to the same State authorities that made the original denial determination with respect to the transfer of the firearm.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idb8fb12a4-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/103/dW/tXI/s1101/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–103, div. W, title XI, § 1101(c)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2022-03-15"},"text":"Mar. 15, 2022","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/136/919"},"text":"136 Stat. 919","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idb8fb12a5-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idb8fb12a6-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDate","id":"idb8fb12a7-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section not effective until Oct. 1 of the first fiscal year beginning after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2022-03-15"},"text":"Mar. 15, 2022","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/103/dW/s4/a"},"text":"section 4(a) of div. W of Pub. L. 117–103","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s6851"},"text":"section 6851 of Title 15","children":[],"tail":", Commerce and Trade."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
